            "title": "Texas Instruments 4Q Sales Rise, Profit Falls",
            "description": "<div class=\"txt-s4 article-text\"><p>\n  By Katherine Hamilton </p><br/><p>\n  Texas Instruments recorded higher revenue in the fiscal fourth quarter, though profit declined slightly. </p><!-- Article --><p>\n\n  The semiconductor company on Tuesday posted a profit of $1.16 billion, or $1.27 a share, in the quarter ended Dec. 31, compared with $1.21 billion, or $1.30 a share, a year earlier. Analysts polled by FactSet were expecting $1.29 a share. </p><p>\n\n  Revenue rose 10% to $4.42 billion. Analysts surveyed by FactSet forecast revenue of $4.44 billion. </p><p>\n\n  Texas Instruments expects revenue in the first quarter to be $4.32 billion to $4.68 billion. Earnings per share are projected to be $1.22 to $1.48. </p><p>\n\n  Analysts polled by FactSet are forecasting revenue of $4.42 billion and earnings of $1.26 a share. </p><br/><p>\n  Write to Katherine Hamilton at katherine.hamilton@wsj.com </p><br/><p>\n  (END) Dow Jones Newswires</p><p>\n\n  01-27-26 1627ET</p></div>",
